Quote:  <i>Kumara</i>, or <i>Kumera, n</i>. (pronounced Koomera), a Maori word for an edible root, the yam or sweet potato, <i>ipomoea batatas, N.O. Convolvulaceae.</i> There are numerous varieties. it should be added that it is doubtful whether it grows wild in New Zealand.
